Step 1: Access the Dataset
1. Navigate to the dataset page: https://nihcc.app.box.com/v/ChestXray-NIHCC/folder/36938765345
2. You may be prompted to create a free Box account or log in to access the files.

Step 2: Download the Dataset
1. Once logged in, locate the dataset folder containing the chest X-ray images and metadata files.
2. Click the “Download” button (or download individual files if needed). 
3. Note that the dataset is large (50+ GB), so ensure you have:
    - Sufficient storage space
    - A stable internet connection
4. After downloading, extract any compressed files (.zip archives).

Step 3: Organize the Files
1. Place all extracted image folders and metadata files into your project directory.
2. Ensure the directory structure matches what your code expects (image folders and CSV/data files in the correct relative paths).

Step 4: Use the Dataset
1. Open the project notebook or script.
2. Update file paths if necessary to point to the downloaded dataset location.
3. Run the code to load, preprocess, and analyze the chest X-ray data.
